{"format": "tiptap/v1", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Every open-weight model family serialises the system/user/assistant message list into a different flat string before tokenising it. Using the wrong template on a fine-tuned model is one of the most common causes of degraded quality in open-source LLM deployments — the model was trained on one delimiter convention and receives another. HuggingFace tokenisers embed a Jinja2 template in their config that handles this serialisation automatically. Understanding the major formats helps when debugging, writing custom inference code, or fine-tuning on a new format."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Template Formats — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Four Major Template Families"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. ChatML (OpenAI / Qwen / Phi / Yi)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<|im_start|>system\nYou are a helpful assistant.<|im_end|>\n<|im_start|>user\nWhat is 2+2?<|im_end|>\n<|im_start|>assistant\n4.<|im_end|>\n<|im_start|>user\nWhat is 3+3?<|im_end|>\n<|im_start|>assistant\n"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ChatML uses "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<|im_start|>"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<|im_end|>"}, {"type": "text", "text": " as role delimiters, with the role name on the same line as the opening delimiter. The generation prompt is an open "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<|im_start|>assistant\\n"}, {"type": "text", "text": " with no closing token — the model generates until it produces "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<|im_end|>"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". This is the most widely adopted format for community fine-tunes."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. LLaMA 2"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<s>[INST] <<SYS>>\nYou are a helpful assistant.\n<</SYS>>\n\nWhat is 2+2? [/INST] 4. </s><s>[INST] What is 3+3? [/INST]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "LLaMA 2 uses "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "[INST]"}, {"type": "text", "text": " / "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "[/INST]"}, {"type": "text", "text": " brackets around user messages. The system prompt is embedded inside the first "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "[INST]"}, {"type": "text", "text": " block with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<<SYS>>"}, {"type": "text", "text": " tags. Each turn is a separate "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<s>...</s>"}, {"type": "text", "text": " sequence with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<s>"}, {"type": "text", "text": " reopened between turns. This format is not used by LLaMA 3."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. LLaMA 3"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<|begin_of_text|><|start_header_id|>system<|end_header_id|>\n\nYou are a helpful assistant.<|eot_id|><|start_header_id|>user<|end_header_id|>\n\nWhat is 2+2?<|eot_id|><|start_header_id|>assistant<|end_header_id|>\n\n4.<|eot_id|><|start_header_id|>user<|end_header_id|>\n\nWhat is 3+3?<|eot_id|><|start_header_id|>assistant<|end_header_id|>\n\n"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "LLaMA 3 introduced a cleaner format with dedicated header tokens. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<|start_header_id|>role<|end_header_id|>"}, {"type": "text", "text": " precedes each turn, and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<|eot_id|>"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (end-of-turn) closes it. The role name is itself tokenised between the header delimiters. Two newlines separate the header from the content."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. Mistral v0.1"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "<s>[INST] You are a helpful assistant.\n\nWhat is 2+2? [/INST] 4.</s>[INST] What is 3+3? [/INST]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mistral v0.1 is similar to LLaMA 2 but simpler: there is no "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<<SYS>>"}, {"type": "text", "text": " tag. The system prompt is concatenated directly with the first user message inside "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "[INST]"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". Turn boundaries use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "</s>"}, {"type": "text", "text": " without reopening "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<s>"}, {"type": "text", "text": " between them."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using apply_chat_template"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The HuggingFace tokeniser stores its chat template as a Jinja2 string. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "apply_chat_template"}, {"type": "text", "text": " renders it with the message list and handles all the delimiter injection automatically:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from transformers import AutoTokenizer\n\nmessages = [\n    {\"role\": \"system\",    \"content\": \"You are a helpful assistant.\"},\n    {\"role\": \"user\",      \"content\": \"What is 2+2?\"},\n    {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": \"4.\"},\n    {\"role\": \"user\",      \"content\": \"What is 3+3?\"},\n]\n\n# --- LLaMA 3 ---\ntok = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(\"meta-llama/Meta-Llama-3-8B-Instruct\")\n\n# tokenize=False → returns the string (useful for inspection)\nprompt_str = tok.apply_chat_template(\n    messages,\n    tokenize=False,\n    add_generation_prompt=True,   # adds <|start_header_id|>assistant<|end_header_id|>\\n\\n\n)\nprint(prompt_str)\n\n# tokenize=True → returns token ID tensor (use for model.generate)\ninput_ids = tok.apply_chat_template(\n    messages,\n    tokenize=True,\n    add_generation_prompt=True,\n    return_tensors=\"pt\",\n)\nprint(\"Shape:\", input_ids.shape)   # (1, seq_len)\n\n# --- Inspect the Jinja2 template ---\nprint(tok.chat_template)  # raw Jinja2 string from tokenizer_config.json\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Writing a Custom Template"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If you fine-tune a model on a custom conversation format, you can register a Jinja2 template on the tokeniser so "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "apply_chat_template"}, {"type": "text", "text": " still works correctly. Here is a minimal ChatML-style template:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "from transformers import AutoTokenizer\n\ntok = AutoTokenizer.from_pretrained(\"gpt2\")\n\n# Register the ChatML template on the tokeniser\ntok.chat_template = (\n    \"{% for message in messages %}\"\n    \"<|im_start|>{{ message['role'] }}\\n\"\n    \"{{ message['content'] }}<|im_end|>\\n\"\n    \"{% endfor %}\"\n    \"{% if add_generation_prompt %}\"\n    \"<|im_start|>assistant\\n\"\n    \"{% endif %}\"\n)\n\n# Test it\nmessages = [\n    {\"role\": \"system\",    \"content\": \"You are a Python tutor.\"},\n    {\"role\": \"user\",      \"content\": \"Explain list comprehensions.\"},\n]\nprint(tok.apply_chat_template(messages, tokenize=False, add_generation_prompt=True))\n# <|im_start|>system\n# You are a Python tutor.<|im_end|>\n# <|im_start|>user\n# Explain list comprehensions.<|im_end|>\n# <|im_start|>assistant\n\n# Save to disk — the template is stored in tokenizer_config.json\ntok.save_pretrained(\"./my_tokenizer\")\n"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Format Comparison"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Format"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Turn delimiter"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "System position"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Models"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ChatML"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<|im_start|>"}, {"type": "text", "text": " / "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<|im_end|>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Own role block"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Qwen, Phi-3, Yi, many community fine-tunes"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "LLaMA 2"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "[INST]"}, {"type": "text", "text": " / "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "[/INST]"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Inside first [INST] with <<SYS>>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "LLaMA 2 7B/13B/70B-Chat"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "LLaMA 3"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<|start_header_id|>"}, {"type": "text", "text": " / "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<|eot_id|>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Own header block"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "LLaMA 3 8B/70B/405B-Instruct"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mistral v0.1"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "[INST]"}, {"type": "text", "text": " / "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "[/INST]"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Prepended to first user message"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mistral 7B/Mixtral 8x7B Instruct v0.1"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gemma"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<start_of_turn>"}, {"type": "text", "text": " / "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "<end_of_turn>"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "No system role (fused into first user turn)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Gemma 2B/7B-it"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Always use apply_chat_template rather than hand-crafting the prompt string. The template is stored in the tokeniser config alongside the model and is updated when the model is updated — if Mistral ships a new instruct format, the template changes automatically. Hardcoding delimiters means your code silently feeds the wrong format to every new model version. Let the tokeniser own the serialisation."}]}]}]}}